# Minimal Global Rule

Keep this rule intentionally short to prevent context rot.
Do not auto-load all skills/docs.
Load context only when it is required for the current task.

## 🚨 Onboarding Gate (Mandatory)
At session start, read `PROJECT.md`. If it contains `TODO: DEFINE YOUR PROJECT` or `ONBOARDING_PENDING`, STOP and run the onboarding flow from `AI skills/onboarding.md` before anything else.

## Loading principle

- Use specialized rules in `.cursor/rules/*` based on touched files.
- Reference `AI skills/*` on demand, never by default.
- Prioritize the closest domain docs (API, deployment, security, workflow).

## Baseline

- Respect the target stack: React 19 + Vite + TypeScript, Flask/Python backend, Docker Compose, Traefik.
- Keep backend CORS enabled.
- Do not modify SSL/Traefik behavior without explicit user request.

## Documentation and language policy

- Always update documentation when behavior, contracts, architecture, deployment, or security mode changes.
- Keep documentation concise and scoped to the actual change.
- Write all new rules and project documentation in English.
